 outbreaks in Spain]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in Spain|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Spain|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Spain|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Spain]]\n", "name_user": "Agathoclea", "label": "safe", "comment": "Redirect bypass fromPrincess Maria Teresa of Bourbon-ParmatoPrincess Mar\u00eda Teresa of Bourbon-Parmausingpopups", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Spain"}
{"title_page": "Bonner Pink", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2016}}\n'''Ralph Bonner Pink''' (30 September 1912 \u2013 6 May 1984) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] politician.\n\nPink was educated at [[Oundle School]] and was a company director. He served as a councillor on [[Portsmouth City Council]] (1948\u201361), then as an [[alderman]], and was [[Lord Mayor of Portsmouth]] for 1961\u201362.\n\nPink was the [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Portsmouth South (UK Parliament constituency)|Portsmouth South]] from 1966 until he died in office in May 1984, aged 71. He was a member of the Speaker's panel of chairmen.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*''The Times Guide to the House of Commons'', [[The Times|Times Newspapers Ltd]], 1966 & 1983\n*{{Rayment-hc|date=March 2012}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Hansard-contribs | mr-bonner-pink | Bonner Pink }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{succession box\n | title  = [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Portsmouth South (UK Parliament constituency)|Portsmouth South]]\n | years  = [[1966 United Kingdom general election|1966]] \u2013 [[1984 Portsmouth South by-election|1984]]\n | before = [[Sir Jocelyn Lucas, 4th Baronet|Sir Jocelyn Lucas, Bt.]]\n | after  = [[Mike Hancock (UK politician)|Mike Hancock]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pink, Bonner}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:1984 deaths]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Councillors in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:People from Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:Lord Mayors of Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:People educated at Oundle School]]\n[[Category:People who died in office]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1966\u20131970]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1970\u20131974]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1974]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1974\u20131979]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1979\u20131983]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1983\u20131987]]\n\n\n{{Conservative-UK-MP-1910s-stub}}\n{{England-mayor-stub}}\n{{England-Conservative-UK-MP-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2016}}\n'''Ralph Bonner Pink''' (30 September 1912 \u2013 6 May 1984) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] politician.\n\nPink was educated at [[Oundle School]] and was a company director. He served as a councillor on [[Portsmouth City Council]] (1948\u201361), then as an [[alderman]], and was [[Lord Mayor of Portsmouth]] for 1961-62.\n\nPink was the [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Portsmouth South (UK Parliament constituency)|Portsmouth South]] from 1966 until he died in office in May 1984, aged 71. He was a member of the Speaker's panel of chairmen.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*''The Times Guide to the House of Commons'', [[The Times|Times Newspapers Ltd]], 1966 & 1983\n*{{Rayment-hc|date=March 2012}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Hansard-contribs | mr-bonner-pink | Bonner Pink }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{succession box\n | title  = [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Portsmouth South (UK Parliament constituency)|Portsmouth South]]\n | years  = [[1966 United Kingdom general election|1966]] \u2013 [[1984 Portsmouth South by-election|1984]]\n | before = [[Sir Jocelyn Lucas, 4th Baronet|Sir Jocelyn Lucas, Bt.]]\n | after  = [[Mike Hancock (UK politician)|Mike Hancock]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pink, Bonner}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:1984 deaths]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Councillors in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:People from Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:Lord Mayors of Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:People educated at Oundle School]]\n[[Category:People who died in office]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1966\u20131970]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1970\u20131974]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1974]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1974\u20131979]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1979\u20131983]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1983\u20131987]]\n\n\n{{Conservative-UK-MP-1910s-stub}}\n{{England-mayor-stub}}\n{{England-Conservativ